Job Profile Summary
Executive Finance & Accounting Professional
Experienced in preparing, examining, and analyzing financial statements, accounting records, and reports to ensure accuracy, completeness, and compliance with standards. Skilled in tax computation, VAT compliance, and preparation of returns, ensuring adherence to regulatory requirements.
Core Competencies:
• 	Budgeting & Financial Control: Develop, maintain, and analyze budgets; prepare variance reports; implement recordkeeping systems; and maintain expenditure controls for operational and project activities.
• 	Financial Analysis & Advisory: Analyze business operations, costs, revenues, commitments, and obligations to project future performance and advise management on resource optimization.
• 	Auditing & Governance: Provide internal and external auditing services, ensuring transparency and compliance with governance frameworks.
• 	Accounting Systems & Technology: Design, implement, and document manual or computer-based accounting and budgeting systems, leveraging modern technology for efficiency.
• 	Strategic Planning: Apply accounting principles to assess past and present operations, forecast revenues and expenditures, and support capital improvement budgeting.
• 	Management Support: Interpret budgets, document revenues and expenditures, and advise executives on effective resource use and assumptions underlying forecasts.
Value Proposition:
A finance leader who combines technical accounting expertise, taxation compliance, and strategic financial planning with strong auditing and governance skills. Adept at leveraging technology to streamline processes, enhance accuracy, and provide actionable insights that strengthen organizational performance and sustainability.
